 North Whitehead; fourth, as an interpreter of philosophical texts and traditions (Kant, Hegel, and Nietzsche no less than Charles Peirce, William James and John Dewey; German idealism as well as American; the Augustinian tradition no less than the pragmatic). Reason, Experience, and God provides an important and comprehensive look at the work of John E. Smith by collected essays which each address aspects of his life-long work. A response by John E. Smith himself draws a line of continuity between the pieces.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Good & Evil.2bisacsh1 aColapietro, Vincent M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeville, Robert C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPotter, Vincent G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoth, Robert J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, John E, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWestphal, Merold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311118960408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z97831107432960 cprintz978082321707640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329646040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823296460423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823296460/original  a978-3-11-074329-6  Fordham University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  a978-3-11-118960-4  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  